title: Adding methods directly to Date and DateConstructor .
body: Adding methods directly to Date and DateConstructor as opposed to creating separate interfaces, reflecting DateJs's direct modification of Date.Prototype and Date, respectively. This allows you to call methods like Date.today() without casting Date to IDateJSStatic, for example (see difference in test file). I reluctantly left in IDateJS and IDateJSStatic so that existing code that uses this definition file will not break, though (for some strange reason) IDateJSStatic used to extend IDateJS, so it is not _totally_ backwards compatible (I have made IDateJSStatic extend DateConstructor, and IDateJS extend Date). That being said, it is trivial to change code that currently uses those interfaces to instead use Date and DateConstructor as appropriate.

title: Added websql type definition
body:
Many existing applications and new applications use the deprecated W3C WebSql specification (http://www.w3.org/TR/webdatabase/) for storing data in a client side database. 
A number of existing tools such as chrome, safari, and the V8/WebKit bowser on Android, support WebSql and will most likely continue to support it into the future. 

This commit contains a basic set of interface definitions to add WebSql functions to TypeScript projects targeting WebSql. 

I ensured that the websql-test.ts file compiles without error.  This is my first DefinitelyTyped pull request, please let me know if any changes are needed to make this WebSql TypeScript definition conformant with DefinitelyTyped's standards.

title: lodash: add _.sum
body:
This adds a definition for the [_.sum](https://lodash.com/docs#sum) function.
There are two things I'm not happy about in this pull request:

---

In this test line:

``` typescript
result = <number>_([4, 2, 8, 6]).sum();
```

If we replace `2` by `'abc'` it still compiles without error. It would be better to enforce that the array is an array of numbers.

---

In this test line:

``` typescript
result = <number>_(stoogesAgesDict).sum(function (stooge) { return stooge.age; });
```

If we replace `stooge.age` by a bogus property like `stooge.xyz` it still compiles without error.

---

Both issues are made more complicated by the lodash wrapping. In the second case, I believe the cause is that when we wrap `stoogesAgesDict` (of type `Dictionary<IStoogesAge>`) by calling `_(stoogesAgesDict)`, the type information for the values of `stoogesAgesDict` is lost and the anonymous function is called with `stooge: any` instead of `stooge: IStoogeAge`.

I'm still relatively new at TypeScript and might have missed the solution for the two issues above. It'd be great if someone could have a second look. :)

The first commit moves everything into a `uri` namespace. This is a breaking change but was done to mirror other libraries like [decimal.js](https://github.com/borisyankov/DefinitelyTyped/blob/575d70adcad0086ec8c6f672a5eb569a4689486c/decimal.js/decimal.js.d.ts) and [moment.js](https://github.com/borisyankov/DefinitelyTyped/blob/575d70adcad0086ec8c6f672a5eb569a4689486c/moment/moment.d.ts). title: ICollectionPromise<T> should extend ng.IPromise with an array of T
body:
ICollectionPromise<T> extends ng.IPromise<T> is the equivalent of
interface IPromise<T> extends ng.IPromise<T> for arrays of T. Therefore
it makes no sense to extend ng.IPromise with just T. Instead it has to
be an array of T.

The consequence of this bug can be observed when calling

Restangular.all('someEntity').getList<SomeEntity>().then((entities) =>
{...})

In this case the TypeScript compiler handles entities as SomeEntity, not
SomeEntity[].

title: Update `WebAuthenticationBroker` class in winrt.d.ts for Windows Phone 8.1
body:
On Windows Phone 8.1 platform, [the `WebAuthenticationBroker` class](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.security.authentication.web.webauthenticationbroker.aspx) has [`authenticateAndContinue` methods](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.security.authentication.web.webauthenticationbroker.authenticateandcontinue.aspx) and [`authenticateSilentlyAsync` methods](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.security.authentication.web.webauthenticationbroker.authenticatesilentlyasync.aspx). I added definitions of these methods.

In addition, [the `WebAuthenticationBroker.authenticateAndContinue(Uri, Uri, ValueSet, WebAuthenticationOptions)` method](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/xaml/dn608116.aspx) receiving a `ValueSet` object as third parameter, I added definition of [the `ValueSet` class](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/xaml/windows.foundation.collections.valueset.aspx).

title: Add overload for http.Server.listen
body:
The backlog parameter should be optional while still accepting the port parameter.

The following program should be valid:

```
var http = require("http");
http.createServer().listen(80, "", function() { console.log("Server started!"); });
```

This pull request adds the missing overload.

The [official documentation](https://nodejs.org/api/http.html#http_server_listen_port_hostname_backlog_callback) shows that the various optional parameters are independent of one another: 

```
server.listen(port[, hostname][, backlog][, callback])
```

Otherwise it would be:

```
server.listen(port[, hostname][, backlog[, callback]])
```
